title: The First DDP Government?
new-page: true
subtitle: A New Cabinet
view-if: year = 1925 and month = 12 and ((next_election_year = 1928 and next_election_month = 12) or next_election_year = 1929)
max-visits: 1
tags: event

= The First DDP Government?

// TODO: Revisit the symmetry between the SPD-compromise and DVP-compromise routes. The current structure gives the player clear parallel options, but future balancing should make the paths feel less symmetrical and more historically/politically distinct.
With pressure mounting over the Expropriation of the Princes, and our poor economic situation, President Hindenburg has decided that a government dependent on toleration is a luxury Germany cannot afford. He has called for a Grand Coalition stretching from the SPD to the DVP. President Hindenburg has even offered our parliamentarian Erich Koch-Weser the chancellorship of this proposed cabinet. However, the SPD have refused to enter the government without a clear set of policies for the new government to follow.

- @spd_compromise: We must persuade the SPD to compromise
- @dvp_compromise: We must persuade the DVP to compromise
- @president: We must work with the President

@spd_compromise
title: We must persuade the SPD to compromise
choose-if: spd_relation > 75 and dvp_relation > 50
unavailable-subtitle: Only possible if SPD relations are over 75 and DVP relations are over 50.
on-arrival: {! 
Q.workers_spd -= 2;
Q.workers_ddp += 1;
Q.old_middle_dvp -= 1;
Q.dvp_relation += 5;
Q.coalition_members = ['spd', 'ddp', 'dvp', 'z'];
Q.coalition_member_list_text = 'SPD + DDP + DVP + Z';
Q.coalition_total_seats = (Number(Q.spd_r) || 0) + (Number(Q.ddp_r) || 0) + (Number(Q.dvp_r) || 0) + (Number(Q.z_r) || 0);
Q.coalition_negotiation_active = 0;
Q.coalition_required_points = 0;
Q.coalition_negotiation_points = 0;
Q.coalition_spd_member = 1;
Q.coalition_kpd_member = 0;
Q.coalition_z_member = 1;
Q.coalition_bvp_member = 0;
Q.coalition_ddp_member = 1;
Q.coalition_dvp_member = 1;
Q.coalition_wp_member = 0;
Q.coalition_dnvp_member = 0;
Q.coalition_nsdap_member = 0;
Q.in_custom_negotiated_coalition = 1;
Q.in_grand_coalition = 1;
Q.in_weimar_coalition = 0;
Q.in_popular_front = 0;
Q.in_left_front = 0;
Q.in_minority_government = 0;
Q.minority_government = 0;
Q.spd_toleration = 0;
Q.ddp_in_government = 1;
Q.spd_in_government = 1;
Q.z_in_government = 1;
Q.bvp_in_government = 0;
Q.dvp_in_government = 1;
Q.wp_in_government = 0;
Q.dnvp_in_government = 0;
Q.kpd_in_government = 0;
Q.nsdap_in_government = 0;
Q.total_ministries = 8;
Q.ddp_ministry_picks = Math.max(1, Math.round(Q.total_ministries * (Number(Q.ddp_r) || 0) / Math.max(1, Q.coalition_total_seats)));
Q.ddp_ministry_picks_remaining = Q.ddp_ministry_picks;
Q.leverage = Q.ddp_ministry_picks;
Q.chancellor = 'Koch-Weser';
Q.chancellor_party = Q.ddp_name || 'DDP';
Q.foreign_minister_party = '';
Q.interior_minister_party = '';
Q.justice_minister_party = '';
Q.labor_minister_party = '';
Q.reichswehr_minister_party = '';
Q.economic_minister_party = '';
Q.finance_minister_party = '';
Q.agriculture_minister_party = '';
!}

The SPD proves reluctant to agree, but under the combined pressure of ourselves, the President, and our allies, they have agreed to a moderate coalition agreement, essentially preserving the status quo. This will be the first government headed by our party, a massive honor for the DDP, and hopefully a sign of better things to come.

- @start_ministries: Continue.

