Despite the pressure of the President, and of ourselves, the SPD has refused to form a government. Instead Erich Koch-Weser and President Hindenburg have persuaded the DVP, Z, and BVP to form a government of the centre, without a commitment from either the SPD or the DNVP to tolerate our government. It's likely that this will be a short lived government.

- @start_ministries: Continue.

